gene_sec <- scran::getTopHVGs( stats, fdr.threshold = 0.05)
st_exp_dis  = st_exp_dis[gene_sec,]

load the weighted matrix

weight_mat = readRDS("./results/kidney/model.L.mat.rds")
adj_matrix = weight_mat$weight_adj[colnames(st_exp_dis),colnames(st_exp_dis)]
row_sums <- rowSums(adj_matrix) 
normalized_matrix <- sweep(adj_matrix, 1, row_sums, FUN = "/")  
normalized_matrix[is.nan(normalized_matrix)] <- 0

w = normalized_matrix

sim_mat_all = calculateSpatialSimMatrix(st_exp =st_exp_dis , w =w )
  
wcor = sim_mat_all$WCor
sim_mat = sim_mat_all$sim_mat

Hierarchical clustering

Add the module score

# Calculating module scores with AddModuleScore, similar to CellTrek
mouse_kid <- AddModuleScore(
object = tks_cluster, 
features = genes_by_group, 
name = 'Module', 
nbin = 10, 
ctrl = 10, 
seed = 42
)

# Visualizing module scores
# Adjusted FeaturePlot to use all relevant module score columns
pfeatures <- FeaturePlot(
object = mouse_kid, 
features = grep('Module', colnames(mouse_kid@meta.data), value = TRUE), 
cols = viridis::viridis(10), pt.size  =0.25
)


# Display the feature plot
pfeatures

##marker gene expression level

markers = c("Pgam2","Slc5a3" )

plotmk = list()
for (k in 1:length(markers)){
  print(k)
  spot_mk1 = st_exp_raw[markers[k],rownames(spot_loc)]
  spot_mk1 = spot_mk1/max(spot_mk1)
  data_mk = data.frame(x = spot_loc[,1],
                       y=  spot_loc[,2],
                       prop  = spot_mk1)
  
  plotmk[[k]] = ggplot(data = data_mk, 
                       mapping = aes(x = x, y = y,color= prop )) +
    geom_point( size = 2)+
    labs(y="",x=" ",title = markers[k], color = "",size= "")+
    theme_classic()+scale_color_viridis() +
    theme(
      axis.ticks = element_blank(), 
      axis.text = element_blank(),
      legend.position = "none",
      panel.border = element_blank(),#element_rect(fill=NA,color="black", size=1, linetype="solid")
      axis.line = element_blank(),
      plot.title = element_text( size=14,hjust = 0.5)
    )
}

gene ontology BP analysis

ctGO_ana1 <- enrichGO(gene = maker1,
                      OrgDb = org.Mm.eg.db,
                      keyType = "SYMBOL",
                      ont = "BP",
                      pvalueCutoff = 0.05,
                      pAdjustMethod = "BH",qvalueCutoff= 0.05)

dotplot(ctGO_ana1 ,showCategory=10,font.size = 8,label_format = 50)

ctGO_ana2 <- enrichGO(gene = maker2,
                      OrgDb = org.Mm.eg.db,
                      keyType = "SYMBOL",
                      ont = "BP",

                      pAdjustMethod = "BH",qvalueCutoff= 0.05)
